Pin the panel time applet to a stable maximum width so the proportional-width
digits of the system font (Inter / similar) don't reflow the panel each second
when seconds are visible.

The applet's content is wrapped in `cosmic::widget::autosize`, so any change in
the rendered text width grows or shrinks the Wayland surface and shifts every
applet to the left of the clock. The fix overlays an invisible "lock" text —
produced by the same formatter chain run against a worst-case timestamp
(Wed, Sep 30 2026, 23:58:58) — under the visible time inside an
`iced::widget::stack`. The first child of `Stack` dictates intrinsic size, so
the lock pins width to the widest possible rendering for the active format
(time-only, time+date, time+date+weekday, or strftime). The visible time is
then centered inside that locked width.

iced 0.14's `Text::color` requires the theme's text class to impl
`From<StyleFn>`, which cosmic's `theme::Text` does not — so the invisible lock
is set via `.class(cosmic::theme::Text::Color(Color::TRANSPARENT))` instead.
The `tnum` font-features alternative is not viable: cosmic-text supports it
but iced 0.14 doesn't surface OpenType features through the `Font` / `Text`
API, so enabling it would require patching iced itself.

